Thus said russotto@vnet.ibm.com (Matthew T. Russotto):
>Who's to say RIPEM's legality won't be debated too?  As I recall, PKP
>claims a patent broad enough to stop ANY public key scheme-- they claim
>to have the use of arithmetic in a public key scheme patented....

RIPEM uses RSAREF which can be licensed from RSA DSI for noncommercial
use.  Read the license yourself, but most people interpret it as meaning
that it's legal to use.  Unless you know something we don't about the
licensing conditions, in which case please share it.
